race.comment: POISED (9) resumes. She only had one run last time in and ran last but it was on heavy ground and she did start $3.40 so it can be excused. Her very early form suggested she had good ability and the stable should have her ready to go off two solid trials. ALIANO (1) resumes having run a close-up fourth on debut at Sandown Lakeside, only beaten 1.1 lengths on that occasion. He can be an improver with a spell under the belt and draws for every chance. BRAZEN DIVA (8) ran well fresh at Mornington over this trip, notching up her fifth minor placing to date. Has the advantage of race fitness now and can go one better. LOUIS BARTHAS (3) resumes having run well at his local debut at Sale last time in. With a bit more time to acclimate, he can run a good race. ROCK GLORY (10) has shown glimpses of ability that have her in the mix.
